<paragraph id="8B8FEE054073FFF5E2D201A73694FB96" blockId="40.[151,1436,940,1072]" pageId="40" pageNumber="191">
The species (
<figureCitation id="130BF2804073FFF5E36C01A73653FC62" box="[297,377,940,965]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1724,1746]" captionTargetBox="[176,1420,1125,1703]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[167,1420,1125,1703]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 32. Trichocerca pediculus Remane. A. Female, lateral; B. SEM photographs of trophi, complete set, dorsal; C. detail left incus and uncus, lateral; D. detail right ramus and uncus, lateral. Scale bars: A: 50 µm; B − D: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240588/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="191">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF8FC224073FFF5E31801A73653FC62" box="[349,377,940,964]" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
A) has not been reported since its description by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA193F44073FFF5E1DF01A6336CFC62" author="Remane" box="[922,1094,940,964]" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" refString="Remane, A. (1949) Die psammobionten Rotatorien der Nord- und Ostsee. Kieler Meeresforschungen, 6, 59 - 67." type="journal article" year="1949">
Remane (
<number id="3DF8FC224073FFF5E64101A73314FC62" box="[1028,1086,940,964]" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" value="1949.0">1949</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
from movable fine sand in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C3095864073FFF5E2D201C4360AFC4E" box="[151,288,975,1000]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pontoporeiidae" genus="Bathyporeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94432174073FFF5E2D201C4360AFC4E" box="[151,288,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="191">Bathyporeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-zone at the Kieler Bucht, Baltic Sea, and Amrum Island, North Sea (
<collectingCountry id="F327AE954073FFF5E61601DB33E8FC4E" box="[1107,1218,976,1000]" name="Germany" pageId="40" pageNumber="191">Germany</collectingCountry>
). In my samples it occurred twice in psammon, 
<number id="3DF8FC224073FFF5E39801FF36D3FBAB" box="[477,505,1012,1037]" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" value="50.0">50</number>
and 
<quantity id="4CC843E04073FFF5E07501FF355DFBAA" box="[560,631,1012,1036]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
from the shoreline of Elba Island, at − 
<number id="3DF8FC224073FFF5E66901FF3362FBAA" box="[1068,1096,1012,1036]" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" value="10.0">10</number>
and − 
<quantity id="4CC843E04073FFF5E6CB01FF33E1FBAA" box="[1166,1227,1012,1036]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" unit="m" value="40.0">40 m</quantity>
; September; water temperature 
<number id="3DF8FC224073FFF5E3610613366AFB96" box="[292,320,1048,1072]" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" value="21.0">21</number>
and 
<number id="3DF8FC224073FFF5E333061336B8FB96" box="[374,402,1048,1072]" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" value="23.0">23</number>
°C.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF4FBE8D4073FFF5E2D204B73391F957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240588/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" targetBox="[176,1420,1125,1703]" targetPageId="40">
<paragraph id="8B8FEE054073FFF5E2D204B73391F957" blockId="40.[151,1435,1724,1777]" pageId="40" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis id="B94432174073FFF5E2D204B73635F974" bold="true" box="[151,287,1724,1746]" pageId="40" pageNumber="191">FIGURE 32.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C3095864073FFF5E36004B735AFF974" authority="Remane. A." authorityName="Remane. A." box="[293,645,1724,1746]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Trichocercidae" genus="Trichocerca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="pediculus">
